  "tips": [
    "For simple data tables, ALWAYS type directly into cells. Never use Insert > Table for basic data entry.",
    "Tab moves to the next column. Enter moves to the next row. This is the fastest way to fill a table.",
    "If Excel opens to the Start Screen, click 'Blank workbook' or press Ctrl+N first.",
    "The workspace (cell grid) occupies most of the window — click anywhere in it to start typing.",
    "When the Start Screen is showing, you must create or open a workbook before you can enter data.",
    "Keyboard shortcuts reference for Excel.",
    "Source: https://support.office.com/en-us/article/keyboard-shortcuts-in-excel-1798d9d5-842a-42b8-9c99-9b7213f0040f",
    "(Custom workflows preserved from existing guide)",
    "Use Tab to move between columns, Enter to move to next row",
    "Type data with Tab characters inline to fill multiple cells in one paste",
    "Formulas start with = sign (e.g., =B2*C2)",
    "Dismiss Document Recovery panel by clicking Close at bottom-left"
